    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:1.1",
          "pli": "Ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā bhikkhū kosalesu viharanti aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā vibbhantacittā pākatindriyā. ",
          "en": "Now at that time several mendicants were staying in the Kosalan lands in a certain forest grove. They were restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, loose-tongued, unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with straying minds and undisciplined faculties. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:1.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anukampikā atthakāmā te bhikkhū saṃvejetukāmā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: ",
          "en": "The deity haunting that forest had compassion for those mendicants, and wanted what’s best for them. So they approached those mendicants wanting to stir them up, and addressed them in verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:2.1",
          "pli": "“Sukhajīvino pure āsuṃ, ",
          "en": "“The mendicants used to live happily, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:2.2",
          "pli": "bhikkhū gotamasāvakā; ",
          "en": "as disciples of Gotama. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:2.3",
          "pli": "Anicchā piṇḍamesanā, ",
          "en": "Desireless they sought alms; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:2.4",
          "pli": "anicchā sayanāsanaṃ; ",
          "en": "desireless they used their lodgings. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:2.5",
          "pli": "Loke aniccataṃ ñatvā, ",
          "en": "Knowing that the world was impermanent "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:2.6",
          "pli": "dukkhassantaṃ akaṃsu te. ",
          "en": "they made an end of suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:3.1",
          "pli": "Dupposaṃ katvā attānaṃ, ",
          "en": "But now they’ve made themselves hard to look after, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:3.2",
          "pli": "gāme gāmaṇikā viya; ",
          "en": "like chiefs in a village. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:3.3",
          "pli": "Bhutvā bhutvā nipajjanti, ",
          "en": "They eat and eat and then lie down, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:3.4",
          "pli": "parāgāresu mucchitā. ",
          "en": "unconscious in the homes of others. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:4.1",
          "pli": "Saṃghassa añjaliṃ katvā, ",
          "en": "Having raised my joined palms to the Saṅgha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:4.2",
          "pli": "idhekacce vadāmahaṃ; ",
          "en": "I speak here only about certain people. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:4.3",
          "pli": "Apaviddhā anāthā te, ",
          "en": "They’re rejects, with no protector, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:4.4",
          "pli": "yathā petā tatheva te. ",
          "en": "just like those who have passed away. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:5.1",
          "pli": "Ye kho pamattā viharanti, ",
          "en": "I’m speaking about "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:5.2",
          "pli": "te me sandhāya bhāsitaṃ; ",
          "en": "those who live negligently. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:5.3",
          "pli": "Ye appamattā viharanti, ",
          "en": "To those who live diligently "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:5.4",
          "pli": "namo tesaṃ karomahan”ti. ",
          "en": "I pay homage.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn9.13:6.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho te bhikkhū tāya devatāya saṃvejitā saṃvegamāpādunti. ",
          "en": "Impelled by that deity, those mendicants were struck with a sense of urgency."
        }
      ],
